  <description>
    <p>
      EngPlayer is a modern, fast, and lightweight media player developed with Python and GTK4 for Linux desktops.
      It serves as a user-friendly entertainment hub that brings your local media library, VOD content, and live streams under one roof.
    </p>
    <p>Key Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><em>IPTV Support:</em> Seamless integration with Xtream Codes API and M3U playlists.</li>
      <li><em>Smart EPG &amp; Catch-up:</em> Real-time program guides and archive playback support.</li>
      <li><em>Recorder (PVR):</em> Record live streams or schedule recordings for later.</li>
      <li><em>Cinematic VOD:</em> Automatic metadata fetching (Posters, Cast, Plot) via TMDb integration.</li>
      <li><em>Trakt.tv Sync:</em> Automatically tracks what you're watching (Scrobbling).</li>
      <li><em>Local Library:</em> Manage your Video, Music, and Picture collections with album art support.</li>
      <li><em>Advanced Player:</em> 10-Band Equalizer, Subtitle download support, and PiP mode.</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

